02:43.271 --> 02:44.271
Oh...

02:45.486 --> 02:46.645
Huh...

02:47.412 --> 02:48.781
this is a surprise.

02:49.158 --> 02:50.181
Hi, Bowie.

02:50.408 --> 02:51.510
Hi, Bowie.

02:51.535 --> 02:52.535
Hi...

02:52.976 --> 02:54.141
so...

02:56.007 --> 02:59.110
I'm trying to come up
with some small talk,

02:59.324 --> 03:00.526
but I can't.

03:00.986 --> 03:02.121
What are you doing here?

03:02.146 --> 03:04.249
Hey, Morgie, look, they have drums.

03:11.575 --> 03:13.643
Well, at least I know she can't walk off

03:13.677 --> 03:15.246
with one of those.

03:16.167 --> 03:18.068
Sorry, that was funnier in my head.

03:18.102 --> 03:20.104
I just wanted you to know...

03:20.137 --> 03:22.205
what you said the last time I saw you...

03:22.772 --> 03:24.367
I really took it to heart.

03:24.809 --> 03:27.145
You were right, about everything.

03:27.622 --> 03:28.644
Oh...

03:28.669 --> 03:31.381
It meant facing some pretty
hard truths about my parenting.

03:31.414 --> 03:33.717
But I'm a much better mom because of it,

03:33.751 --> 03:36.087
and Morgan is definitely a happier kid.

03:36.393 --> 03:37.902
MIRANDA: No more acting out.

03:39.490 --> 03:41.065
I'm really proud of her,

03:41.692 --> 03:42.972
and proud of you, too.

03:43.800 --> 03:45.504
So it's okay that we
stopped by to see you?

03:45.835 --> 03:47.804
She asks about you all the time.

03:47.838 --> 03:49.977
My mom has a new boyfriend.

03:50.624 --> 03:52.364
Oh, does she?

03:52.743 --> 03:53.811
What's his name?

03:53.844 --> 03:55.579
I call him "Not Bowie."

03:55.612 --> 03:57.281
Well, that's a weird name.

03:59.350 --> 04:00.835
She misses you.

04:01.018 --> 04:04.054
And we heard that you're giving
guitar lessons these days.

04:04.079 --> 04:05.664
Guess who wants to learn how to play?

04:05.689 --> 04:07.624
- I do!
- Uh...

04:08.624 --> 04:10.019
Would you be willing to...?

04:10.044 --> 04:11.298
I'd love to,

04:11.595 --> 04:12.679
but...

04:12.983 --> 04:15.019
my schedule's kind of
booked up right now.

04:15.118 --> 04:17.334
You don't want to because you hate me.

04:18.535 --> 04:20.103
Morgan!

04:20.223 --> 04:22.192
Look, I do not hate you.

04:22.317 --> 04:23.609
Not even a little bit.

04:24.974 --> 04:27.777
All right, you know what?
I have some time right now.

04:28.812 --> 04:30.014
Are you ready to do this?

04:30.046 --> 04:31.681
I was born ready.

04:31.714 --> 04:32.816
Yeah.

04:33.498 --> 04:34.823
Go check out some guitars.

04:34.848 --> 04:36.150
See if there's one you like.

04:39.165 --> 04:41.568
You are the most amazing person.

04:41.600 --> 04:42.836
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

04:42.869 --> 04:45.954
Hey, she's not the only
one who's missing you.

04:47.706 --> 04:49.408
But... you have a boyfriend.

04:50.102 --> 04:51.410
He really is...

04:51.444 --> 04:52.578
not you.

04:52.948 --> 04:55.849
Well... I'm engaged.

04:58.350 --> 04:59.319
Oh.

04:59.352 --> 05:00.528
Oh!

05:00.840 --> 05:02.109
Wow.

05:02.489 --> 05:05.258
- That's wonderful!
- BOWIE: Yeah.

05:05.290 --> 05:06.927
You're getting married!

05:07.373 --> 05:08.608
I am!

05:09.362 --> 05:11.064
Congratulations.

05:12.331 --> 05:14.166
To who?

05:14.199 --> 05:15.442
♪ ♪

05:17.887 --> 05:21.273
AMBER: Okay, so Andi has
the breakfast sandwich,

05:21.298 --> 05:23.166
Buffy has the fiesta scramble,

05:23.305 --> 05:25.452
and Cyrus has the berry smoothie.

05:25.477 --> 05:27.579
Actually, that was blueberry pancakes.

05:27.604 --> 05:30.040
- Fine, if you're gonna be picky.
- ANDI: Wait.

05:30.065 --> 05:31.767
- Jonah hasn't ordered.
- JONAH: Oh!

05:31.792 --> 05:32.852
No worries.

05:32.877 --> 05:33.877
I'm good, thanks.

05:35.187 --> 05:36.555
You're not hungry?

05:36.588 --> 05:38.725
(CHUCKLES) Then why did
you come to breakfast?

05:38.758 --> 05:40.360
Yeah, you could have slept in.

05:40.393 --> 05:42.638
I'm fine.
I'm just here to enjoy your company.

05:42.874 --> 05:44.398
That's sweet!

05:44.575 --> 05:45.683
And weird...

05:45.708 --> 05:47.701
This guy claims this
isn't what he ordered.

05:47.734 --> 05:48.835
Stupid, right?

05:48.867 --> 05:50.011
- CYRUS: Totally.
- JONAH: So dumb.

05:50.035 --> 05:51.038
You're a great waitress.

05:51.071 --> 05:53.501
Anyway, I'm supposed to toss this.

05:53.865 --> 05:55.041
Do you want it?

05:55.066 --> 05:57.403
Oh, well, if it's just going
to go to waste, sure.

05:57.710 --> 05:59.346
- Enjoy.
- Thanks.

06:03.383 --> 06:04.383
(QUIETLY): Oh, man.

06:07.420 --> 06:09.222
What? Should I wait?

06:09.254 --> 06:11.057
No, no, go ahead.

06:13.692 --> 06:15.294
That was pretty nice of her, huh?

06:17.030 --> 06:18.631
Amber's a nice person.

06:20.365 --> 06:21.434
Not that nice.

06:21.468 --> 06:22.592
