06:33.946 --> 06:36.064
Guess what I just finished addressing!

06:37.083 --> 06:38.184
Congress.

06:38.218 --> 06:39.686
No, silly,

06:39.718 --> 06:41.220
your wedding invitations.

06:41.254 --> 06:43.290
They're all ready for you to mail.

06:43.323 --> 06:44.891
Look how beautiful.

06:44.924 --> 06:48.562
Ooh, I didn't realize I was
having a royal wedding.

06:48.595 --> 06:52.032
Well, it won't be a junkyard
hootenanny, if that's what you mean.

06:52.064 --> 06:53.600
They're very beautiful, Mom.

06:53.633 --> 06:54.903
Thank you. (CHUCKLES)

06:55.735 --> 06:57.369
I was going to mail them myself,

06:57.394 --> 06:59.570
since I designed them, and ordered them,

06:59.595 --> 07:00.747
and addressed them,

07:00.772 --> 07:01.921
and stamped them,

07:01.946 --> 07:04.036
and pick the date that's on them.

07:04.382 --> 07:05.545
But you should do it.

07:05.578 --> 07:07.160
It's your special day.

07:11.603 --> 07:13.372
Hi, Bex...

07:13.404 --> 07:14.769
Hey...

07:14.794 --> 07:17.164
Well, if it isn't Melinda.

07:17.301 --> 07:20.571
Here to accuse us of losing
something your daughter stole?

07:20.596 --> 07:22.565
Actually, Bowie just
told me the good news.

07:22.590 --> 07:25.427
I came to congratulate
you on your engagement.

07:26.252 --> 07:27.632
Thank you...?

07:27.771 --> 07:28.865
(SCOFFS) Sure.

07:28.890 --> 07:32.117
It's all sweetness and light until
someone loses a Tibetan prayer box.

07:32.802 --> 07:35.593
Oh, that's right.
You're the grandmother.

07:36.313 --> 07:39.639
Oh, and she's also headed to
the back office, right, Mom?

07:39.664 --> 07:43.864
Where I will be watching this entire
exchange on the security cameras.

07:43.955 --> 07:45.811
Just FYI.

07:47.958 --> 07:49.661
She is fun.

07:49.694 --> 07:51.095
We enjoy her.

07:51.128 --> 07:53.732
I really did just come to
give you my best wishes.

07:53.779 --> 07:56.810
I get that I blew my chance to be
friends with you a long time ago,

07:56.835 --> 07:58.971
but I truly am happy for you.

07:59.003 --> 08:00.306
Well, thank you.

08:00.338 --> 08:02.518
- If you really mean it.
- I do.

08:02.741 --> 08:05.093
You and Bowie make
such a perfect couple.

08:05.591 --> 08:07.927
I just wish my relationship
with Morgan's father

08:07.952 --> 08:09.628
was more like yours.

08:10.681 --> 08:12.818
Instead of, well... (IMITATES EXPLOSION)

08:12.850 --> 08:14.233
Oh...

08:14.720 --> 08:16.718
Can I ask what caused the...
(IMITATES EXPLOSION)

08:17.203 --> 08:19.039
Honestly?

08:19.130 --> 08:21.032
I never saw it coming.

08:21.057 --> 08:24.171
For six years, we had
a pretty perfect relationship.

08:24.196 --> 08:25.364
And then...?

08:25.951 --> 08:28.534
And then, we got married.

08:28.788 --> 08:30.468
Really?

08:30.501 --> 08:31.703
Well, what happened?

08:31.737 --> 08:34.897
Suddenly it felt like we were
together because we had to be,

08:34.953 --> 08:36.746
and not because we wanted to be.

08:37.288 --> 08:39.792
We started spending
more time apart, and then,

08:39.985 --> 08:43.504
eventually it felt like we were living
two completely different lives...

08:43.875 --> 08:45.874
until we couldn't remember

08:46.083 --> 08:48.053
why we were together in the first place.

08:48.553 --> 08:50.689
Oh... sounds awful.

08:50.722 --> 08:52.020
Oh, don't worry!

08:52.045 --> 08:53.915
That's not gonna happen
to you and Bowie.

08:53.940 --> 08:56.343
You guys have what it takes
to make a marriage work.

08:56.594 --> 08:58.187
♪ ♪

09:04.035 --> 09:06.804
- So... Morgan.
- Present.

09:06.831 --> 09:08.468
Your mom says I can trust you.

09:08.493 --> 09:09.615
I know I was bad.

09:09.640 --> 09:11.500
But I promise, I'm on my best behavior.

09:12.073 --> 09:13.186
Cross your heart?

09:13.211 --> 09:14.851
I'll keep my hands
where you can see them.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.113
Good.

09:16.141 --> 09:17.443
Now, let's choose you a guitar.

09:17.510 --> 09:19.719
Like in <i> Harry Potter?</i>
When they choose you a wand?

09:20.171 --> 09:21.687
Yeah, kind of.

09:21.719 --> 09:24.189
Do you have mahogany
and dragon heartstring?

09:25.116 --> 09:26.650
(SUCKS TEETH) No, but
I'm sure I can find you

09:26.674 --> 09:28.869
a mahogany and...

09:29.413 --> 09:30.581
mahogany.

09:30.704 --> 09:31.757
Sure!

09:32.204 --> 09:33.650
One sec.

09:34.031 --> 09:35.446
Let's see...

09:35.486 --> 09:37.457
you'll need something
on the small side...

09:38.348 --> 09:39.348
Yeah.

09:40.584 --> 09:42.116
How 'bout this?

09:42.707 --> 09:44.060
♪ ♪

09:45.876 --> 09:47.094
Morgan?

09:47.712 --> 09:49.415
I can't see your hands!

09:56.221 --> 09:57.542
♪ ♪

09:58.756 --> 10:00.163
Morgan!

10:02.593 --> 10:03.593
Morgan!

10:04.663 --> 10:06.665
Did anyone see a little girl
with long blond hair?

10:08.265 --> 10:09.901
Uh, no...

10:09.934 --> 10:11.350
It's fine, she's just one of those kids

10:11.374 --> 10:13.102
that likes to play games. It's...

10:13.972 --> 10:15.406
Morgan!

10:15.640 --> 10:17.696
You win! You can come out now!

10:18.270 --> 10:20.038
Trust me, she's fine.

10:20.278 --> 10:21.713
Morgan!

10:21.746 --> 10:23.023
♪ ♪

10:23.814 --> 10:25.416
BUFFY: We could go to a movie.

10:25.449 --> 10:26.828
It's too nice a day to go to the movies.

10:26.852 --> 10:28.487
Let's do something outside.

10:28.520 --> 10:29.755
Okay, Mom.

10:29.788 --> 10:31.990
Hey! Sometimes, they are right.

10:32.022 --> 10:33.057
Not hiking.

10:33.091 --> 10:34.267
I don't want to get another tick.

10:34.291 --> 10:36.664
That wasn't a tick, that was a pen mark.

10:36.689 --> 10:37.767
We don't know that for sure.

10:37.791 --> 10:39.437
It was on your shirt.

10:39.462 --> 10:40.885
And it was blue.

10:40.910 --> 10:44.102
If it looks like a tick, and if it sends
you down a fear spiral like a tick,

10:44.127 --> 10:45.663
then it may as well be a tick!

10:45.688 --> 10:48.256
This is exactly what I wanted to do,

10:48.281 --> 10:49.783
talk about ticks all day.

10:49.808 --> 10:51.977
- (SCOFFS)
- Unless you have a better idea.

10:52.010 --> 10:53.511
Let's go to Adrenaline City.

10:53.544 --> 10:55.158
We haven't been there in forever!

10:55.183 --> 10:56.852
BUFFY: And they have a
new roller coaster!

10:56.885 --> 10:59.926
I have motion sickness patches,
we're good to go!

11:00.017 --> 11:01.819
Sounds fun.

11:01.888 --> 11:03.568
Um, but I think I'm gonna
sit this one out.

11:03.765 --> 11:05.033
Seriously?

11:05.058 --> 11:07.861
Yeah, I'm just not really
feeling Adrenaline City today.

11:07.886 --> 11:09.283
Well, we could do something else.

11:09.308 --> 11:11.023
No, I... have some weekend homework

11:11.048 --> 11:12.482
I should probably start anyway.

11:12.507 --> 11:14.949
Homework? On a Saturday morning?

11:15.206 --> 11:17.709
Jeez, what's the opposite
of Adrenaline City?

11:17.734 --> 11:19.034
Snooze Town.

11:19.059 --> 11:20.580
Okay, guys, cool it.

11:20.605 --> 11:22.405
He doesn't have to come
if he doesn't want to.

11:22.864 --> 11:25.700
- Did I hear someone say Adrenaline City?
- Yeah!

11:25.845 --> 11:29.437
I heard their new roller coaster makes
one out of three people throw up.

11:29.462 --> 11:32.265
Odds are one of us could be
re-tasting our breakfast.

11:32.290 --> 11:34.573
Doesn't that make you
want to come, Jonah?

11:34.598 --> 11:35.993
Jonah's not coming?

11:36.449 --> 11:37.775
Are you sure?

11:37.839 --> 11:40.350
Because I happen
to have two free tickets,

11:40.375 --> 11:42.042
and one of them could be yours.

11:42.163 --> 11:43.556
Yeah, why not?

11:44.468 --> 11:46.081
You guys are right. What'd they say?

11:46.106 --> 11:48.075
"You can... do homework
when you're dead?"

11:48.237 --> 11:49.806
Actually, I think it's "sleep,"

11:49.839 --> 11:51.675
but who cares? You're coming!

11:52.976 --> 11:54.812
Unexpected twist.

11:54.844 --> 11:56.779
Okay, I'll just go change real quick.

11:56.813 --> 11:58.145
Hold up for a minute.

12:01.050 --> 12:04.689
- Hey, thanks for that.
- I'm glad you're coming.

12:06.055 --> 12:07.824
You know what's going
on here, don't you?

12:07.858 --> 12:09.392
There's something going on?

12:09.425 --> 12:10.527
Tell us.

12:10.560 --> 12:11.916
♪ ♪

12:12.362 --> 12:14.968
Jonah and Amber
are getting back together.

12:15.332 --> 12:16.461
