13:00.109 --> 13:02.349
<i>♪ I'm honest, when I
say you're flawless ♪</i>

13:02.512 --> 13:03.557
<i>♪ Move me like the comets ♪</i>

13:03.581 --> 13:05.080
<i>♪ Rocket ship and put me on it ♪</i>

13:05.989 --> 13:08.325
<i>♪ Na na na na na na na na na ♪</i>

13:08.350 --> 13:11.186
<i>♪ Na na na na na na na Ooh-ooh ♪</i>

13:11.211 --> 13:14.900
<i>♪ Na na na na na na na na na Ooh ♪</i>

13:14.925 --> 13:17.060
<i>♪ Na na na na na ♪</i>

13:17.093 --> 13:19.896
- (SCREAMING)<i>
- ♪ I'm a woman, I'm gonna own it ♪</i>

13:19.930 --> 13:22.866
<i>♪ So baby build a rocket
ship and put me on it ♪</i>

13:22.898 --> 13:24.703
(VOCALIZING)

13:28.805 --> 13:31.309
<i>♪ Like a woman, and I want it ♪</i>

13:31.334 --> 13:33.905
<i>♪ So baby build a rocket
ship and put me on it ♪</i>

13:33.930 --> 13:35.805
See? They're a couple.

13:35.830 --> 13:36.888
No, they're not.

13:36.913 --> 13:38.365
Jonah is dating Libby.

13:38.520 --> 13:39.545
Andi.

13:39.570 --> 13:41.402
They're sharing a pretzel.

13:41.498 --> 13:43.301
That's basically middle school marriage.

13:43.326 --> 13:45.795
Guys, I really don't think that
that's what's going on here.

13:45.820 --> 13:48.925
And yet, we have the evidence
right in front of us.

13:49.126 --> 13:50.651
Dipped in mustard.

13:50.676 --> 13:53.613
Jonah didn't even want to come
today until Amber invited him.

13:53.638 --> 13:56.176
And what about his new free
food privileges at the Spoon?

13:57.560 --> 13:58.795
She's still not convinced.

13:59.727 --> 14:01.428
(SCOFFS) How could you not be?

14:03.164 --> 14:04.574
Unless...

14:04.608 --> 14:06.481
she knows something we don't.

14:06.683 --> 14:07.928
Like what?

14:08.534 --> 14:09.680
Like what?

14:09.713 --> 14:11.009
♪ ♪

14:13.022 --> 14:14.374
Morgan!

14:14.516 --> 14:15.718
Morgan!

14:17.651 --> 14:18.686
Morgan!

14:20.617 --> 14:21.617
Morgan?

14:22.577 --> 14:23.577
Morgan?

14:24.760 --> 14:25.825
Bowie!

14:27.353 --> 14:28.406
(SIGHS) Miranda...

14:28.431 --> 14:29.733
What's wrong? Where's Morgan?

14:30.105 --> 14:31.448
Look, I am so sorry.

14:31.473 --> 14:32.828
For what? You're scaring me.

14:32.853 --> 14:34.596
I just took my eyes
off her for a second...

14:35.945 --> 14:38.091
- (SIGHS) she disappeared.
- Disappeared?

14:38.116 --> 14:39.346
You lost her?!

14:39.371 --> 14:42.175
Look, I don't know what to do, I've
been looking everywhere for her.

14:42.852 --> 14:44.096
I think we should call the police.

14:44.120 --> 14:45.255
- Boo!
- (MIRANDA LAUGHS)

14:46.288 --> 14:47.827
Did you see his face?

14:47.852 --> 14:49.434
I did, Morgie! He was so worried!

14:49.531 --> 14:51.531
Wait... did you know where
she was this whole time?

14:51.847 --> 14:52.941
Yeah.

14:53.128 --> 14:54.888
She does this with me, too.

14:55.217 --> 14:57.094
Once in an airport!

14:57.513 --> 14:59.615
What can I do? It's her favorite game.

14:59.648 --> 15:01.684
- It's fun!
- Not for me.

15:01.716 --> 15:04.019
Oh, come on. Don't be mad.

15:04.666 --> 15:05.666
(SIGHS)

15:06.839 --> 15:08.256
Ugh, what's the point?

15:08.281 --> 15:09.749
No! Please, tell me.

15:09.774 --> 15:11.109
What were you gonna say?

15:11.359 --> 15:12.461
Why?

15:12.494 --> 15:14.233
So you can show up in a few weeks,

15:14.497 --> 15:16.866
thank me for my honesty, and
tell me how much I helped you?

15:16.898 --> 15:18.378
♪ ♪

15:18.403 --> 15:20.272
Find someone else to play games with.

15:20.350 --> 15:21.451
I'm out.

15:23.605 --> 15:24.840
Are we getting Bowie back?

15:26.042 --> 15:27.509
No, sweetie.

15:27.542 --> 15:28.777
♪ ♪

15:32.204 --> 15:35.058
This is the first time I'm
showing this to anyone.

15:35.329 --> 15:36.912
What is it?

15:39.053 --> 15:41.645
It's the wish Jonah made
at the Moon Festival.

15:41.896 --> 15:43.331
It fell off his lantern.

15:43.356 --> 15:45.625
Jonah's never really
mastered the glue stick.

15:45.650 --> 15:47.486
I didn't ask him about it at the time

15:47.511 --> 15:50.147
because we'd just invented
the "no break up" break up.

15:50.172 --> 15:52.112
And then I thought I should
wait for him to bring it up,

15:52.136 --> 15:53.505
but he never did.

15:53.530 --> 15:56.050
- And then all this time passed...
- Just show it to us already!

16:00.455 --> 16:02.854
"I wish my family could be happy again."

16:03.785 --> 16:05.587
What's going on with Jonah's family?

16:05.732 --> 16:08.222
I think they might be
having money problems.

16:08.535 --> 16:10.036
How do you get that?

16:10.069 --> 16:13.305
Well, he hasn't been ordering
anything when we're at the Spoon...

16:13.338 --> 16:16.008
And he didn't want to go
to Adrenaline City

16:16.041 --> 16:17.810
until Amber offered up a free ticket.

16:17.843 --> 16:20.479
That's why Amber's been
hooking him up with stuff.

16:20.512 --> 16:21.647
She must know.

16:21.680 --> 16:23.449
He probably confided in her

16:23.482 --> 16:25.986
because her family went
through something similar.

16:26.019 --> 16:27.854
That's why they've
seemed so close lately.

16:27.886 --> 16:29.946
Not because they're dating.

16:30.756 --> 16:32.763
Gosh, and I was so judge-y!

16:33.392 --> 16:34.994
I feel horrible.

16:35.028 --> 16:37.197
I wish there was something
we could do for him.

16:37.230 --> 16:40.067
Well, we can respect his privacy.

16:40.099 --> 16:41.901
And not jump to conclusions.

16:42.443 --> 16:43.689
But...

16:43.714 --> 16:45.693
right now, that's about it.

16:47.006 --> 16:48.037
Yeah...

16:48.358 --> 16:49.587
Yeah.

16:51.376 --> 16:52.397
Or...

16:52.704 --> 16:53.904
♪ ♪

16:56.745 --> 16:57.852
And it turns out,

16:57.877 --> 17:00.480
Morgan was with Miranda the whole time.

17:00.505 --> 17:01.573
What?!

17:01.598 --> 17:03.095
Those two are like the bad seed,

17:03.120 --> 17:04.723
and the bad tree it came from.

17:04.748 --> 17:06.832
I can't believe I ever dated her.
(GROANS)

17:07.529 --> 17:09.492
You know, she came to see me, too?

17:10.554 --> 17:12.050
- She did?
- Yeah.

17:12.075 --> 17:15.058
And she... said some
things that were scary.

17:15.083 --> 17:16.145
Like what?

17:18.268 --> 17:19.402
Just things.

17:19.426 --> 17:20.551
I don't remember,

17:20.577 --> 17:22.847
all I know is that they scared me.

17:25.348 --> 17:27.028
You gotta get her out of your head.

17:27.250 --> 17:28.325
♪ ♪

17:28.526 --> 17:29.792
You should, too.

17:31.088 --> 17:32.292
Yeah.

17:33.317 --> 17:34.450
(MOANS SOFTLY)

17:35.574 --> 17:36.941
This is nice.

17:38.729 --> 17:40.308
We should do this more often.

17:41.421 --> 17:43.401
BOWIE: I'm so lucky.

17:43.433 --> 17:45.298
To have this family.

17:45.695 --> 17:47.264
To have you back in my life.

17:47.498 --> 17:51.169
To think that I ever
stepped away from it,

17:51.194 --> 17:53.064
- even just for a minute...
- Hey...

17:53.478 --> 17:54.912
You're here.

17:55.239 --> 17:56.708
I'm here.

17:57.882 --> 18:00.118
Our giant hole in the wall is here.

18:00.390 --> 18:01.692
BOWIE: It's true.

18:02.579 --> 18:04.115
I love our life together.

18:06.268 --> 18:08.549
<i>- ♪ There's a hole in the world ♪</i>
- Hope it never changes.

18:09.427 --> 18:11.855
<i>♪ In the shape of you ♪</i>

18:13.325 --> 18:15.873
- Me, too.<i>
- ♪ And it doesn't matter ♪</i>

18:15.898 --> 18:18.267
<i>♪ What I do ♪</i>

18:18.803 --> 18:21.785
<i>♪ I'll always be ♪</i>

18:22.606 --> 18:25.911
<i>♪ Half of two ♪</i>

18:26.718 --> 18:27.952
Hey, guys.

18:27.977 --> 18:29.412
Dad, we need to talk to you.

18:29.980 --> 18:31.744
Ooh, opening with "Dad."

18:31.769 --> 18:32.904
This must be serious.

18:32.929 --> 18:33.932
It is!

18:33.957 --> 18:35.846
- So be serious.
- Okay.

18:36.346 --> 18:38.896
Can you please give Jonah a job here?

18:39.489 --> 18:42.032
Whoa... why?

18:42.406 --> 18:44.302
I... can't tell you.

18:44.327 --> 18:45.796
Yes, you can.

18:45.829 --> 18:47.074
I'm "Dad."

18:47.965 --> 18:49.100
(SIGHS)

18:49.227 --> 18:50.696
Look, I'm really sorry, guys.

18:50.721 --> 18:52.623
But this is a small business.

18:52.648 --> 18:54.550
We can barely afford
the staff we have now.

18:54.971 --> 18:56.424
So much for that idea.

18:56.506 --> 18:57.931
Hey!

18:58.114 --> 19:00.039
Hey, I'm really sorry, dude.

19:00.064 --> 19:01.278
For what?

19:01.312 --> 19:03.075
Not being able to give you the job

19:03.100 --> 19:04.702
they said you needed.

19:05.248 --> 19:06.578
(SCOFFS) Why would you say that?

19:06.825 --> 19:09.472
We just... really wanted to help.

19:09.653 --> 19:10.897
Help?

19:11.370 --> 19:12.822
Help with what?

19:17.012 --> 19:18.326
♪♪

19:25.397 --> 19:27.199
How did you find out?

19:27.232 --> 19:29.168
The night of the Moon Festival,

19:29.202 --> 19:31.238
your wish fell off your lantern.

19:31.270 --> 19:33.723
Well, that explains why it
didn't come true. (SCOFFS)

19:34.273 --> 19:36.008
What does it mean?

19:36.041 --> 19:38.682
You don't have to talk about
it if you don't want to.

19:39.775 --> 19:42.648
It's just... embarrassing.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.818
Dude, you've seen me on a carousel.

19:45.457 --> 19:48.884
After which,
I proceeded to vomit into my shoe.

19:53.225 --> 19:55.094
Sometime last year, my...

19:55.127 --> 19:57.196
my dad made an investment...

19:57.230 --> 19:59.405
which I guess went extremely bad.

19:59.965 --> 20:03.002
I didn't know anything about it
until a couple months ago,

20:03.036 --> 20:04.703
when my parents told me we...

20:04.736 --> 20:06.171
had to declare bankruptcy.

20:06.587 --> 20:08.993
I think of that as a board game word...

20:09.408 --> 20:11.043
not a real life word.

20:11.077 --> 20:13.280
It's kind of the same,

20:13.312 --> 20:15.275
except you don't lose your game piece.

20:16.115 --> 20:18.385
You, uh, you lose your actual house.

20:18.763 --> 20:20.433
Where are you living?

20:23.122 --> 20:24.557
We're staying with relatives.

20:24.589 --> 20:26.059
- Jonah...
- I'm fine!

20:26.091 --> 20:27.412
Really. (SIGHS)

20:29.228 --> 20:30.860
We have a place to stay.

20:31.443 --> 20:33.113
We're still all together.

20:34.166 --> 20:35.401
It's just hard.

20:35.434 --> 20:36.469
Listen,

20:36.501 --> 20:38.305
people declare bankruptcy

20:38.338 --> 20:40.040
all the time.

20:40.072 --> 20:41.273
They get through it,

20:41.307 --> 20:43.276
they come out the other side.

20:43.309 --> 20:44.478
You will, too.

20:46.479 --> 20:48.248
That felt good telling you.

20:49.427 --> 20:51.830
It's like I just took off
a really heavy backpack.

20:52.374 --> 20:53.655
- (JONAH CHUCKLES)
- CYRUS: Dude,

20:53.685 --> 20:56.155
you can always lean on us.

20:56.188 --> 20:58.021
We want you to.

20:58.083 --> 20:59.914
It makes us feel useful.

21:00.359 --> 21:02.315
You don't have to keep secrets.

21:02.595 --> 21:05.043
You can tell us the stuff
you think you can't.

21:05.330 --> 21:06.532
Got it?

21:08.300 --> 21:09.690
Got it...

21:10.190 --> 21:11.905
No more secrets.

21:11.937 --> 21:13.258
♪♪

21:18.677 --> 21:21.313
Hi! Can I just give these to you?

21:21.347 --> 21:23.650
You sure can. Hand them over!

21:23.683 --> 21:25.151
Ooh.

21:25.184 --> 21:27.252
- Are these wedding invitations?
- Yeah.

21:27.286 --> 21:29.356
These are nice!

21:29.388 --> 21:32.192
Professional-grade calligraphy,

21:32.224 --> 21:34.493
limited edition flourishing love stamps.

21:34.527 --> 21:36.328
Silver foil embellishments.

21:36.361 --> 21:37.529
Oh, it was all my mom.

21:37.562 --> 21:39.366
You know, this is my
favorite part of the job,

21:39.398 --> 21:41.552
getting to be a part of this
important moment

21:41.577 --> 21:43.913
when someone's life
is gonna change forever.

21:44.236 --> 21:46.372
- Um...
- Hey! What?!

21:46.405 --> 21:48.674
I don't think I'm gonna mail
these out today after all.

21:48.707 --> 21:50.635
- I'm not... they're not ready.
- But...

21:50.660 --> 21:52.312
I-I just want to spell check them again.

21:52.345 --> 21:54.047
Don't want people having
to choose between

21:54.079 --> 21:55.682
"tricken" and..."boof."

21:55.714 --> 21:57.259
♪♪

22:02.187 --> 22:03.857
Days like these,

22:03.889 --> 22:06.092
I wonder why I even
put on my short shorts.

22:10.251 --> 22:12.184
Wait, stop, we gotta go back.

22:12.209 --> 22:14.398
- I can't find my phone.
- It's in your hand.

22:15.867 --> 22:17.302
Great, it's happening.

22:17.336 --> 22:18.580
I'm gonna be one of those old people

22:18.604 --> 22:20.481
looking for the glasses that
are already on their face.

22:20.505 --> 22:22.674
I think you already are that old person.

22:22.707 --> 22:24.253
I'd like to argue with you, but I found

22:24.277 --> 22:25.894
a piece of hard candy in my pocket.

22:25.991 --> 22:27.359
(BUFFY GIGGLES)

22:27.579 --> 22:28.867
Is that Jonah?

22:29.682 --> 22:30.983
CYRUS: He's with Amber.

22:31.017 --> 22:33.053
I'm really glad he's had
Amber to confide in.

22:33.086 --> 22:34.854
She's been through it, so she knows.

22:34.886 --> 22:37.523
I can't believe I thought they
were actually back together.

22:37.557 --> 22:39.692
They were a toxic couple.

22:39.724 --> 22:42.028
I'm sure neither one of
them wants to revisit that.

22:42.060 --> 22:43.362
But they really work as friends.

22:43.395 --> 22:44.867
They really do.

22:45.464 --> 22:46.693
♪♪

22:53.372 --> 22:55.409
Any one else feel like
their eyes are burning?

